clopedia of the Eastern Front | year=2002 | place=Garden City, NY | publisher=The Military Book Club| isbn=978-0-73943-128-3|ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Glantz |first=David |title=Barbarossa Derailed: The Battle for Smolensk, Volume 1 |publisher=Helion & Company |year=2010a |isbn=978-1906033729 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Glantz |first=David |title=Barbarossa Derailed: The Battle for Smolensk, Volume 2 |publisher=Helion & Company |year=2010b |isbn=978-1906033903 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Glantz |first = David |title=Operation Barbarossa: Hitler's invasion of Russia 1941 |publisher=The History Press |year=2012 |isbn=978-0752460703 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |author1-last = Glantz |author1-first = David |author2-last = House |author2-first = Jonathan |title=When Titans Clashed: How the Red Army Stopped Hitler |publisher=University Press of Kansas |year=2015 | volume=Revised and Expanded Edition|isbn=978-0-70062-121-7 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Gorodetsky |first=Gabriel |authorlink=Gabriel Gorodetsky |title=Grand Delusion: Stalin and the German Invasion of Russia |publisher=Yale University Press |year=2001 |isbn=978-0300084597 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Guderian |first = Heinz |title=Panzer Leader |place=Cambridge, MA |publisher=Da Capo Press |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-30681-101-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Handrack |first=Hans-Dieter |title=Das Reichskommissariat Ostland: Die Kulturpolitik Der Deutschen Verwaltung Zwischen Autonomie Und Gleichschaltung 1941\u20131944 |publisher=Gauke |location=Hann. M\u00fcnden |language=German |year=1981 |isbn=978-3879980383 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book| last=Hanson | first=Victor Davis | year=2017 | title=The Second World Wars: How the First Global Conflict Was Fought and Won | place= New York | publisher=Basic Books | isbn=978-0-46506-698-8| ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Hartmann |first=Christian |authorlink=Christian Hartmann (historian)|title=Operation Barbarossa: Nazi Germany's War in the East,