ile:Miss Magnolia Medal.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Magnolia Medal]] - Awarded to any member or former member of the Mississippi National Guard, or any of the armed services of the United States, who distinguishes themselves through outstanding service or extraordinary achievement in behalf of the Mississippi National Guard.\n* [[File:Miss Commendation.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Commendation Medal]] -  May be awarded to any member or former member of the Mississippi National Guard for meritorious service or meritorious achievement on behalf of the state of Mississippi.\n* [[File:Miss Medal of Efficiency.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Medal of Efficiency]] - Awarded to enlisted members of the active Mississippi National Guard who have over five (5) years honorable service in the active Mississippi National Guard and have exhibited exemplary behavior, efficiency and loyalty to their unit and the Mississippi National Guard.\n* [[File:Miss War Medal.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi War Medal]] -Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard for honorable service in the Armed Forces of the U.S. during National Emergency declared by the Congress.\n* [[File:Miss Emergency Service.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Emergency Service Medal]] - Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard for honoraqble service to the State of Mississippi for duty performed during a major tour of state emergency duty declared by the Adjutant General.\n* [[File:Miss Service School Medal.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Service School Medal]] - Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard upon successful completion of any Service School conducted by the active military services while a member of the active Mississippi National Guard not serving in active federal service.\n* [[File:IANG Medal of Valor.png|80px]] [[Mississippi Longevity Medal]] - Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard for each of a combination of four (4) years of honorable service in the active National Guard of Mississippi.\n* [[File:Miss Recruiting Medal.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Recruiting Medal]] - Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard who obtains three new members for any unit of the organized militia.\n* [[File:USA - MS Soldier of the Year.png|80px]] [[Mississippi Soldier of the Year Ribbon]] - First issued in 2012, unknown in order of precedence.\n\n== [[Missouri]] ==\nMissouri National Guard State Awards:\n<div style=\"float:left; width:100%;\">\n* [[File:Meritorious Service Medal Missouri National Guard.svg|80px]] Missouri Meritorious Service Medal\n* [[File:Missouri Conspicuous Service Medal.svg|80px]] Missouri Conspicuous Service Medal\n* [[File:Missouri Commendation Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Commendation Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri Desert Storm Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Desert Storm Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri 20 Year Long Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri 20 Year Long Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri 15 Year Long Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri 15 Year Long Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri 10 Year Long Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri 10 Year Long Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri 5 Year Long Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri 5 Year Long Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri First Sergeant Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri First Sergeant Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri Expeditionary Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Expeditionary Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri State Emergency Duty Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri State Emergency Duty Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri Panamanian Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Panamanian Service Ribbon\n* [[File:USA - MO Afghanistan Campaign.svg|80px]] Missouri Afghanistan Campaign Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri Kosovo Campaign Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Kosovo Campaign Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri Recruiting and Retention Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Recruiting and Retention Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri Adjutant General's Twenty Ribbon.svg|80px]] [[Marksmanship Badges (United States)#Adjutant General.27s Marksmanship Awards|Missouri Adjutant General's Twenty Ri