''Washington Legion of Merit Medal (WSLM)''' - This decoration shall be awarded to any person who has distinguished himself/herself in the performance of exceptionally meritorious service and/or outstanding achievements as member or in affiliation to the State of Washington. The performance must be such as to merit recognition for service that is clearly exceptional over an extended period of time or achievements conspicuously greater than those appropriate for lesser decorations. \n* [[File:USA - WA Cross of Valor.png|80px]] '''Washington Cross of Valor''' (Discontinued as of 30 September 1998)\n* [[File:USA - WA Aviation Cross.png|80px]] '''Washington Aviation Cross Medal''' (Discontinued as of 30 September 1998)\n* [[File:WAGM.jpg|80px]] '''Washington Guardsman Medal (WSGM)''' - This decoration shall be awarded to any person who demonstrates extreme courage in the performance of a heroic act involving personal hazard or danger. This decoration may not be awarded solely on the basis of having saved a life.\n* [[File:WAMSM.jpg|80px]] '''Washington Meritorious Service Medal (WSMSM)''' - This decoration shall be awarded to any person who has distinguished himself/herself by performing meritorious service and/or achievements, as a member or in affiliation with the Military Department, State of Washington. This decoration is awarded for service over an extended period of time or achievements conspicuously greater than those appropriate for award of the WSCM. This decoration is not appropriate for presentation as an impact award. \n* [[File:WACM.jpg|80px]] '''Washington Commendation Medal (WSCM)''' - This decoration shall be awarded to any person who distinguishes himself/herself by heroism, and/or extraordinary duty performance, as a member or in affiliation with the Military Department, State of Washington. This decoration is awarded for accomplishments of a lesser degree and shorter service duration than required for award of the WSMSM. This decoration is appropriate for presentation as an impact award.\n* [[File:WAAM.jpg|80px]] '''Washington Achievement Medal (WSAM)''' - This decoration shall be awarded to any person who distinguishes himself/herself by specific acts and/or achievements resulting in enhanced or increased unit readiness, operations, morale, or mission accomplishment, as a member or in affiliation with the Military Department, State of Washington. This decoration is awarded for accomplishments of a lesser degree and shorter service duration than required for the WSCM. The WSAM is appropriate for presentation as an impact award. \n* [[File:WASMR.jpg|80px]] '''Washington Strength Management Ribbon (WSSMR)''' - Previously known as the Washington State Distinguished Recruiting Ribbon it was renamed 31 January 1999. This ribbon shall be awarded to anyone who recruits an individual or causes a Soldier to reenlist/extend (retention attributed to a specific Soldier) during a one-year period. Only one award will be given in any one-year period. Full-time recruiting force personnel and Soldiers on orders as recruiter aides are ineligible for this award.\n* [[File:USA - WA Defense Service Military Ribbon.png|80px]] '''Washington State Defense Service Ribbon (WSDSR)''' (Discontinued - 31 December 1994; Reestablished 18 June 2002) - This ribbon shall be awarded to any Soldier of the Washington Army National Guard inducted into Active Federal Service (title 32 or 10) upon declaration of an emergency by the President of the United States or for special operations at any time between 07 December 1943 to 31 December 1994 and after 11 September 2001. \n* [[File:WAESR.jpg|80px]] '''Washington Emergency Service Ribbon (WSESR)''' - Previously known as the Washington State Disaster Relief Ribbon from 03 May 1963 to 31 December 1994. This ribbon shall be awarded to any person ordered by the governor into state active duty or to any individual(s) providing support services during a declared state of emergency. An individual must work one day (minimum of eight hours) in order to be eligible to receive this award. \n* [[File:WANGSR.jpg|80px]] '''Washington National Guard Service Ribbon (WANGSR)''' - This ribbon is awarded to any Soldier of the Washington Army National Guard upon completion of fiver years of satisfactory service in any of the Armed Forces of the United States, or components thereof. The soldier must be a member of the WAARNG when the ribbon is presented. Regardless of the number of years of service beyond five, the recipient will receive only one initial ribbon upon assignment to the WAARNG or WSG. Thereafter, the Soldier will receive subsequent awards at five year increments so long as they are otherwise entitled. The individual's pay entry base date (PEBD) will be used to determine year of service for this award. \n* [[File:USA - WA Good Conduct Medal Ribbon.png|80px]] '''Washington Good Conduct Medal''' (Discontinued as of 31 December 1994)\n* [[File:WAUC.jpg|80px]] '''Washington Unit Citation Ribbon (WSUCR)''' (''Right Side'') - This ribbon shall be awarded to each member of a Washington Army National Guard unit or Washington State Guard which is cited by TAG or a higher military headquarters for notable achievement, such as winning the Eisenhower Trophy, the Draper Armor Award, or the Superior Unit Award. Only one unit citation will be awarded to a unit during a single calendar year regardless of the number of notable achievements. Only those who were members of the unit during the period for which the citation was earned will wear the award. Soldiers who received the ribbon may continue to wear it when transferred. Individuals transferring into a cited unit who are not otherwise entitled, will not be authorized the ribbon. The Washington State Unit Citation will not be awarded in conjunction with the Army Superior Unit Award. \n\n'''Washington Air National Guard Awards:'''\n\n* [[File:USA - WA Air National Guard Aviation Cross.png|80px]] Washington Air National Guard Aviation Cross\n* [[File:ANG Aerial Achievement Medal.png|80px]] Washington Air National Guard Aerial Achievement Medal\n* [[File:USA - WA Air National Guard Distinguished Recruiting Award Ribbon.jpg|80px]] Washington Air National Guard Distinguished Recruiting Award\n\n== [[West Virginia]] ==\nWest Virginia National Guard State Awards:\n* [[File:SDNG Distinguished Service Award.png|80px]] West Virginia Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:WVNG Legion of Merit.png|80px]] West Virginia Legion of Merit\n* [[File:WVNG Meritorious Service Medal.png|80px]] West Virginia Meritorious Service Medal\n* [[File:WVNG Commendation Medal.png|80px]] West Virginia Commendation Medal\n* [[File:WVNG Achievement Medal.png|80px]] West Virginia Achievement Medal\n* [[File:WVNG Emergency Service Ribbon.png|80px]] West Virginia Emergency Service Ribbon\n* [[File:WVNG State Service Ribbon.png|80px]] West Virginia State Service Ribbon\n* [[File:WVNG Service Ribbon.png|80px]] West Virginia Service Ribbon\n* [[File:WVNG Minuteman Ribbon.png|80px]] West Virginia Minuteman Ribbon\n* [[File:WVNG Distinguished Unit Award.png|80px]] West Virginia Distinguished Unit Award\n\n== [[Wisconsin]] ==\nWisconsin National Guard State Awards:\n* [[File:Wounded Action Medal.JPG|80px]] Wisconsin Meritorious Service Medal\n* [[File:Meritorious Service Medal.JPG|80px]] Wisconsin Meritorious Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Duty Ribbon.JPG|80px]] Wisconsin Department of Military Affairs Commendation Medal\n* [[File:Distinguished Service Medal1.JPG|80px]] Wisconsin Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:Recruiting Bar Ribbon.JPG|80px]] Wisconsin National Guard Recruiting Bar\n* [[File:Service Ribbon.JPG|80px]] Wisconsin National Guard Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Emergency Service Ribbon1.JPG|80px]] Wisconsin National Guard Emergency Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Write Medal.JPG|80px]] Wisconsin National Guard Write Medal\n* [[File:Texas Desert Shield-Desert Storm Campaign Medal Ribbon.svg|80px]] Wisconsin National Guard Southwest Asia Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Eisenhower Trophy Unit Ribbon.JPG|80px]] Eisenhower Trophy Unit Citation\n* [[File:Berlin Crisis Ribbon.JPG|80px]] Berlin Crisis Ribbon\n* [[File:Wortham Achievement Service Ribbon.png|80px]] Wisconsin Wortham Achievement Service Ribbon\n\n== [[Wyoming]] ==\n[[:File:WY NG awards.jpg|Wyoming National Guard State Awards]]\n* [[File:Wyoming Medal for Excellence.JPG|80px]] Wyoming National Guard Association Medal for Excellence\n* [[File:USA - WI Distingushed Service Medal Ribbon.png|80px]] Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:Guard Meritorious Achievement Ribbon.svg|80px]] Meritorious Achievement Medal\n* [[File:USA - WI Outstanding Service.png|80px]] Outstanding Service Ribbon\n* [[File:USA - WI Exceptional Achievement Ribbon.png|80px]] Exceptional Achievement Ribbon\n* [[File:Achivement ribbon of the Wyoming National Guard.svg|80px]] Achievement Ribbon\n* [[File:USA - AL National Emergency.png|80px]] Berlin Crisis Ribbon\n* [[File:Distinguished Service Medal1.JPG|80px]] Selected Reserve Force Ribbon\n* [[File:USA - WY National Guard Service Ribbin.png|80px]] Wyoming National Guard Service Ribbon\n* [[File:USA - WY State Active Duty Ribbon.png|80px]] State Active Duty Ribbon\n* [[File:Guard Recruiting Ribbon.svg|80px]] Wyoming National Guard Recruiting Ribbon\n* [[File:Albtr.png|80px]] Wyoming Active Duty Basic Training Ribbon\n;No longer authorized for wear\n* [[File:Wyoming 5 year Service Medal.JPG|80px]] Wyoming Air National Guard 5-year Service Medal\n* [[File:Wyoming 10 year Service Medal.JPG|80px]] Wyoming Air National Guard 10-year Service Medal\n* [[File:Service Medal1.JPG|80px]] Wyoming Philippine Campaign Medal\n\n==See also==\n* [[Awards and decorations of the state defense forces]]\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n==Further reading==\n\n*{{Cite book |last=Lewis |first=Kenneth C.\n|title=Military medals, awards, and service badges of Iowa |publisher = Kenneth C. Lewis|year=1976|OCLC=2372611}}\n*Borgmann, Fred J. (2013) Wisconsin Military And Civil Medals publisher Fred J. Borgmann, Iola, Wisconsin\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110719164939/http://www.omsa.org/photopost/showgallery.php?cat=510 State Medals - The OMSA Medal Database]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101116202214/http://armyawards.com/arng/arng.shtml Armyawards.com Army National Guard]\n*[http://ultimaterack.ajandj.com/ Ultimate Rack]\n*[http://www.medals.pl/us/ U.S. Decorations Ribbon Rackbuilder]\n*[https://store.nwtmint.com/Military_Medals/National_Guard_Service_Ribbons/ALL/ Northwest Territorial Mint]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Awards And Decorations Of The National Guard}}\n[[Category:Awards and decorations of the United States National Guard| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date = March 2019}}\n{{Short description|United States military awards for national guard forces}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date = March 2019}}\n\n'''Awards and decorations of the National Guard''' are presented to members of the [[United States National Guard]] and sometimes to members of the [[state defense force]]s in addition to regular [[Awards and decorations of the United States military|United States military decorations]]. Each of the [[state government]]s of the [[United States]] maintains a series of military decorations for issuance to members of the [[National Guard of the United States|National Guard]], with such awards presented under the authority of the various [[State Adjutant General|state adjutants general]].\n\nThose National Guard soldiers and airmen who subsequently serve in the active or reserve federal forces of the [[United States Army]], [[United States Navy|Navy]], [[United States Marine Corps|Marine Corps]], [[United States Coast Guard|Coast Guard]], or [[United States Air Force]] (i.e., as active duty or reserve members of the Army, Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps, or Coast Guard) may not continue to wear and display such decorations on a military uniform, unless such activation is under Title 32 status. Active duty regulations allow federal soldiers, airmen, sailors and marines to accept but not to wear state awards.\n\nMost states authorize the wear of other states' awards if a soldier or airman has earned awards from a state or territory to which he or she is not presently assigned. The order of precedence is typically the presently assigned state, followed by awards from the [[District of Columbia]], then other states by their [[List of U.S. states by date of statehood|order of admission]].\n\nThe following is a list of National Guard decorations, as issued by each of [[U.S. state|the fifty]] United States; [[Puerto Rico]], [[Guam]], the [[U.S. Virgin Islands]], and the [[District of Columbia]].\n\n== [[Alabama]] ==\nAlabama National Guard State Awards:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://al.ng.mil/ALABAMA/pages/StateAwards.aspx |title=State Awards |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website= |publisher=[[Alabama National Guard]] |access-date=10 April 2018 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n<div style=\"float:left; width:100%;\">\n* [[File:Aldsm.svg|80px]] Alabama Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:Alcom.svg|80px]] Alabama Commendation Medal\n* [[File:Alpcdr.svg|80px]] Alabama [[Phenix City]] Civil Disturbance Medal\n* [[File:Aldsr.png|80px]] Alabama Operation Desert Storm Ribbon\n* [[File:USA - AL Veteran Service.png|80px]] Alabama Veterans Service Medal\n* [[File:USA - AL National Emergency.png|80px]] Alabama National Emergency Service Medal\n* [[File:Alssr.png|80px]] Alabama Special Service Medal\n* [[File:Alfsr.png|80px]] Alabama Faithful Service Medal\n* [[File:AR Recruiting Ribbon.svg|80px]] Alabama Recruiting Ribbon\n* [[File:Albtr.png|80px]] Alabama Active Duty Basic Training Medal\n</div>{{Clear}}\n\n== [[Alaska]] ==\n<div style=\"float:left; width:100%;\">\nAlaska National Guard State Awards:<ref>AKNGM 1616.01, enclosure G (14 Apr 17)</ref>\n\n* [[File:AZ Recruiting Ribbon.png|80px]] Alaska Decoration of Honor \n* [[File:Noribbon.svg|80px]] Alaska Heroism Medal \n* [[File:GASelectedReserveRbn1.JPG|80px]] Alaska Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:Alaska National Guard Legion of Merit Ribbon.jpg|80px]] Alaska Legion of Merit\n* [[File:Noribbon.svg|80px]] Alaska Meritorious Service Medal \n* [[File:AK Air Medal.PNG|80px]] Alaska Air Medal\n* [[File:Alaska National Guard - Commendation.JPG|80px]] Alaska Commendation Medal\n* [[File:Noribbon.svg|80px]] Alaska Achievement Medal \n* [[File:USA - Alaska Humanitarian Award.png|80px]] Alaska Humanitarian Service Medal\n* [[File:USA - Alaska State Service Medal.png|80px]] Alaska State Service Medal\n* [[File:USA - Alaska Community Service Medal.png|80px]] Alaska Community Service Medal\n* [[File:Domestic Emergency Ribbon.png|80px]] Alaska Domestic Emergency Ribbon\n* [[File:Alaska National Guard - Pistol Marksms Medal.JPG|80px]]  Alaska Marksmanship Medal\n* [[File:AK Homeland Security Medal.PNG|80px]] Alaska Homeland Security Medal\n* [[File:AR Recruiting Ribbon.svg|80px]] Alaska Recruiting Ribbon\n* [[File:Noribbon.svg|80px]] Alaska State Partnership Program Ribbon \n* [[File:Cold War Victory Medal ribbon.svg|80px]]  Alaska Cold War Victory Ribbon\n* [[File:Alaska Territorial Guard Medal.PNG|80px]] Alaska Territorial Guard Medal \n* [[File:Alaska National Guard - Governor's Distinguished Unit Citation.png|80px]] Alaska Governor's Distinguished Unit Citation \n* [[File:Noribbon.svg|80px]] Adjutant General's Marksmanship Proficiency Award (Badge)\n* [[File:Noribbon.svg|80px]] Governor's Twenty Award (Tab)\n\n\n\n</div>{{Clear}}\n\n== [[Arizona]] ==\nArizona National Guard State Awards:\n\n* [[File:AZ Medal of Valor.png|80px]] Arizona Medal of Valor\n* [[File:USA - AZ AG Medal.png|80px]] Arizona Adjutant General's Medal\n* [[File:AZ Distinguished Service Medal.png|80px]] Arizona Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:AZ Meritorious Service Medal.png|80px]] Arizona Meritorious Service Medal\n* [[File:AZ Exceptionally Long Service Medal.png|80px]] Arizona Exceptionally Long Service Medal\n* [[File:GASelectedReserveRbn1.JPG|80px]] Arizona Long Service Medal\n* [[File:AZ Service Ribbon.png|80px]] Arizona Service Ribbon\n* [[File:AZ Military Academy OCS.png|80px]] Arizona Military Academy Ribbon (OCS) \n* [[File:AZ Military Academy NCO.png|80px]] Arizona Military Academy Ribbon (NCO)  (No longer awarded)\n* [[File:AZ Southwest Asia Service Support Ribbon.png|80px]] Arizona Southwest Asia Service Support Ribbon\n* [[File:AZ State Active Duty Service Ribbon.png|80px]] Arizona State Active Duty Service Ribbon\n* [[File:AZ Re-enlistment Ribbon.png|80px]] Arizona Re-enlistment Ribbon  \n* [[File:AZ Community Service Ribbon.png|80px]] Arizona Community Service Ribbon\n* [[File:AZ Initial Active Duty for Training Ribbon.png|80px]] Arizona Initial Active Duty for Training Ribbon  (No longer awarded)\n* [[File:AZ Recruiting Ribbon.png|80px]] Arizona Recruiting Ribbon\n* [[File:AZ Honor Attendance Ribbon.png|80px]] Arizona Honor Attendance Ribbon  (No Longer Awarded)\n\n== [[Arkansas]] ==\nArkansas National Guard State Awards:\n* [[File:Arkansas National Guard Medal of Honor Ribbon.JPG|80px]] Arkansas Medal of Honor\n* [[File:USA - AL Military Medal.png|80px]] Arkansas Military Medal\n* [[File:Arkansas NG DSM.JPG|80px]] Arkansas Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:Arkansas NG Exceptional Service.JPG|80px]] Arkansas Exceptional Service Medal\n* [[File:AR Commendation Medal.PNG|80px]] Arkansas Commendation Medal\n* [[File:AR Federal Service Ribbon.PNG|80px]] Arkansas Federal Service Ribbon\n* [[File:AR Service Ribbon.PNG|80px]] Arkansas Service Ribbon\n* [[File:AR Emergency Service Ribbon.PNG|80px]] Arkansas Emergency Service Ribbon\n* [[File:USA - Arkansas Homeland Defense.png|80px]] Arkansas Homeland Defense Ribbon\n* [[File:Guard Recruiting Ribbon.svg|80px]] Arkansas Recruiting Ribbon\n\n== [[California]] ==\n[https://web.archive.org/web/20070625012242/http://www.calguard.ca.gov/casmr/awards2.htm California National Guard State Awards]:\n\n* [[File:CA Medal of Valor.