069_2420_2425.html| archivedate= 2 September 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n* [[File:Michigan Medal for Valor.png|80px]] - Michigan Medal for Valor\n* [[File:Michigan Distinguished Service Medal.png|80px]] - Michigan Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:Michigan Lifesaving Medal.png|80px]] - Michigan Lifesaving Medal\n* [[File:Michigan Legion of Merit.png|80px]] - Michigan Legion of Merit\n* [[File:Michigan Recruiting Ribbon.png|80px]] - Michigan Recruiting Ribbon\n*[[File:Honor Guard Ribbon.png|80x80px]] - Michigan Honor Guard Ribbon\n* [[File:Michigan Broadsword Service Medal.png|80px]] - Michigan Broadsword Service Medal\n* [[File:Michigan Active State Service Ribbon.png|80px]] - Michigan Active State Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Michigan State War on Terrorism Ribbon.png|80px]] - Michigan State War on Terrorism Ribbon\n*[[File:Michigan Outside U.S. Service Ribbon.png|80x80px]] - Michigan Outside U.S. Service Ribbon\n*- Michigan Outside U.S. Training Ribbon\n* [[File:Michigan State Partnership Ribbon.png|80px]] - Michigan State Partnership Ribbon\n\n== [[Minnesota]] ==\nMinnesota National Guard State Awards:\n\n* [[File:Minnesota National Guard Distinguished Service Medal.png|80px]] Minnesota Distinguished Service Medal\n* [[File:MN Medal for Valor.png|80px]] Minnesota Medal for Valor\n* [[File:MN Medal for Merit.png|80px]] Minnesota Medal for Merit\n* [[File:MN Commendation Medal.png|80px]] Minnesota Commendation Medal\n* [[File:Minnesota Achievement Ribbon.svg|80px]]Minnesota Achievement Ribbon\n* [[File:MN Good Conduct Ribbon.png|80px]] Minnesota Good Conduct Ribbon\n* [[File:MN Active Duty Ribbon.png|80px]] Minnesota State Active Duty Ribbon\n* [[File:Ilmilat.jpg|80px]] Minnesota Distinguished Recruiting Ribbon\n* [[File:MN Service Medal.png|80px]] Minnesota Service Ribbon\n\n== [[Mississippi]] ==\nMississippi National Guard State Awards<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ms.ng.mil/resources/generalstaff/g6/daphotos/Documents/MS%20Ribbons.pdf |title=Ribbons |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website= |publisher=[[Mississippi National Guard]] |access-date=11 April 2018 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n* [[File:Miss Medal of Honor.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Medal of Honor]]\n* [[File:Miss Magnolia Cross.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Magnolia Cross]] - Awarded to any member or former member of the Mississippi National Guard who has distinguished themselves by exceptionally meritorious service in a duty of great responsibility, or by unselfish and untiring activities while in state service or in support of the Mississippi National Guard, has rendered a distinct service in furthering the security and welfare of the state.\n* [[File:Miss Magnolia Medal.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Magnolia Medal]] - Awarded to any member or former member of the Mississippi National Guard, or any of the armed services of the United States, who distinguishes themselves through outstanding service or extraordinary achievement in behalf of the Mississippi National Guard.\n* [[File:Miss Commendation.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Commendation Medal]] -  May be awarded to any member or former member of the Mississippi National Guard for meritorious service or meritorious achievement on behalf of the state of Mississippi.\n* [[File:Miss Medal of Efficiency.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Medal of Efficiency]] - Awarded to enlisted members of the active Mississippi National Guard who have over five (5) years honorable service in the active Mississippi National Guard and have exhibited exemplary behavior, efficiency and loyalty to their unit and the Mississippi National Guard.\n* [[File:Miss War Medal.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi War Medal]] -Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard for honorable service in the Armed Forces of the U.S. during National Emergency declared by the Congress.\n* [[File:Miss Emergency Service.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Emergency Service Medal]] - Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard for honoraqble service to the State of Mississippi for duty performed during a major tour of state emergency duty declared by the Adjutant General.\n* [[File:Miss Service School Medal.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Service School Medal]] - Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard upon successful completion of any Service School conducted by the active military services while a member of the active Mississippi National Guard not serving in active federal service.\n* [[File:IANG Medal of Valor.png|80px]] [[Mississippi Longevity Medal]] - Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard for each of a combination of four (4) years of honorable service in the active National Guard of Mississippi.\n* [[File:Miss Recruiting Medal.JPG|80px]] [[Mississippi Recruiting Medal]] - Awarded to any member of the Mississippi National Guard who obtains three new members for any unit of the organized militia.\n* [[File:USA - MS Soldier of the Year.png|80px]] [[Mississippi Soldier of the Year Ribbon]] - First issued in 2012, unknown in order of precedence.\n\n== [[Missouri]] ==\nMissouri National Guard State Awards:\n<div style=\"float:left; width:100%;\">\n* [[File:Meritorious Service Medal Missouri National Guard.svg|80px]] Missouri Meritorious Service Medal\n* [[File:Missouri Conspicuous Service Medal.svg|80px]] Missouri Conspicuous Service Medal\n* [[File:Missouri Commendation Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Commendation Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri Desert Storm Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Desert Storm Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri 20 Year Long Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri 20 Year Long Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri 15 Year Long Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri 15 Year Long Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri 10 Year Long Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri 10 Year Long Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri 5 Year Long Service Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri 5 Year Long Service Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri First Sergeant Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri First Sergeant Ribbon\n* [[File:Missouri Expeditionary Ribbon.svg|80px]] Missouri Expeditionary