a Rica|Costa Rica]] (2), [[2006 FIFA World Cup Group A#Ecuador vs Germany|Ecuador]] (2), [[2006 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Germany vs Argentina|Argentina]]\n*[[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]] vs [[2010 FIFA World Cup Group D#Germany vs Australia|Australia]], [[2010 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Germany vs England|England]], [[2010 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Argentina vs Germany|Argentina]] (2)\n| align=center rowspan=2| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/07/09/us-soccer-world-ger-klose-goals-idUSKBN0FD2L520140709 |title=Miroslav Klose's World Cup goals |work=Reuters | first =Karolos | last= Grohmann |date=2014-07-08 |accessdate=2014-07-30}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 16\n| {{dts|2014|7|8|format=dmy}}\n| {{success|'''2'''\u20130}}\n| [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]\n| align=center| [[Brazil v Germany (2014 FIFA World Cup)|7\u20131]]\n| [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014, Brazil]] <br> [[2014 FIFA World Cup#Semi-finals|Semi-final]]\n|}\n\n==Top goalscorers for each tournament==\n[[File:Fontaine1958.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Just Fontaine scored a record 13 goals at the 1958 FIFA World Cup.|alt=Just Fontaine with the ball during a game]]\n[[File:Eusebio Portugal.JPG|thumb|Eus\u00e9bio scored nine goals for Portugal at the 1966 World Cup.|alt=A portrait of Eus\u00e9bio]]\n[[File:James Rodr\u00edguez.jpg|thumb|James Rodr\u00edguez scored six goals for Colombia at the 2014 World Cup.|alt=James Rodr\u00edguez with his arms high]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|+ Top goalscorers at each FIFA World Cup final tournament<ref>{{cite report|title=FIFA World Cup: Statistics|format=PDF|publisher=FIFA|date=October 2007|url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/fifafacts/mencompwc/51/97/30/ip-301_01a_fwc-stats.pdf|accessdate=2015-09-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|author= Kolur, Nihal |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2018/07/15/world-cup-golden-ball-award-past-winners-best-players |title=Golden Ball Winners in World Cup History |magazine=Sports I